{"id":"274902730_A_stronger_bound_for_the_strong_chromatic_index","abstract":"We prove $\\chi_s'(G)\\leq 1.93 \\Delta(G)^2$ for graphs of sufficiently large\nmaximum degree where $\\chi_s'(G)$ is the strong chromatic index of $G$. This\nimproves an old bound of Molloy and Reed. As a by-product, we present a\nTalagrand-type inequality where it is allowed to exclude unlikely bad outcomes\nthat would otherwise render the inequality unusable.","authors":["Henning Bruhn","Felix Joos"],"meta":["April 2015Electronic Notes in Discrete Mathematics 49","DOI:10.1016/j.endm.2015.06.038","SourcearXiv"],"references":["220441883_Concentration_of_Multivariate_Polynomials_and_Its_Applications","2125429_A_Strong_Edge-Coloring_of_Graphs_with_Maximum_Degree_4_Using_22_Colors","265458700_Introduction_to_Coding_Theory","263012349_Induced_Matchings_in_Graphs_of_Bounded_Maximum_Degree","259106337_Induced_Matchings_in_Subcubic_Graphs","256935755_A_Bound_on_the_Strong_Chromatic_Index_of_a_Graph","256157945_Induced_matchings_in_bipartite_graphs","248413997_Weighted_sums_of_certain_dependent_variables","244514149_The_strong_chromatic_index_of_graphs","242380529_Counting_cycles_and_finite_dimensional_L_p_norms","236736804_On_the_method_of_bounded_differences","233981901_On_the_Method_of_Typical_Bounded_Differences","231923497_A_Large_Deviation_Inequality_for_Functions_of_Independent_Multi-Way_Choices","229706634_Induced_matchings_in_cubic_graphs","228562753_Extensions_to_McDiarmid's_inequality_when_differences_are_bounded_with_high_probability","224983649_The_Distance-t_Chromatic_Index_of_Graphs","222481215_The_maximum_number_of_edges_in_2K","222472913_Coloring_Graphs_with_Sparse_Neighborhoods","220357968_Concentration_For_Independent_Permutations","220191815_The_strong_chromatic_index_of_a_cubic_graph_is_at_most_10","220187663_Induced_matchings_in_bipartite_graphs","38370094_Weighted_sums_of_certain_dependent_variables","2373306_Concentration_Of_Measure_And_Isoperimetric_Inequalities_In_Produc